cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NI, cs.SE

The paper deals with the problem of identifying the topology of distribution grids using data from smart sensors. This involves the estimation of line parameters of Ohm equation for topology identification, which is a problem in system identification (cs.SY). The paper also introduces a learning method for hidden-node detection and impedance calculation, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.AI, cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of dealing with uncorrelated data, unavailability of phasor measurements, and unbalanced systems, which are topics in networked systems (cs.NI) and software engineering (cs.SE).
